devdoc.author: Kent Miguel
devdoc.details: uses chainlink automation to end register, voting, and count phases

countVotes().details: see pointer below: 1. If a candidate has >= 50% of the votes + 1 then he/she is the winner 2. ...if no winner in round 1, go to the next round and distribute the 2nc choice of the 1st choice voters of the eliminated candidate(s) 3. count again

enterCandidate(string).details: will be registered to vote automatically and will be disabled when register phase is over

registerToVote().details: 1. users who enter as a candidate will be registered automatically, will be disabled at the end of phase 1 2. Optimize this by accessing struct once and store it in a local variable and use that for the checks.. see coverage first and gas viewer

vote(address,address,address).details: come back to implement checks: 1. phase switches 2. flags: isRegistered, hasVoted 3. Update points for candidate structs

withdrawCandidate().details: checks:      1 . disabled when register phase is over      2. check that person who registered are only the one who can withdraw      3. check that cannot withdraw if entry does not exist

devdoc.title: A Ranked Choice Voting Smart Contract

countVotes().notice: this function calculates the votes to get the winner

registerToVote().notice: this function register voters to vote for phase 2: Voting

vote(address,address,address).notice: this function allows voters to vote their choices in the election
